<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="67087" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">Male.</emphasis>
Measurements (in mm): Body length 1.35; carapace 0.60 length, 0.40 width; abdomen 0.70 length, 0.35 width. Leg measurements: I 2.15 (0.55, 0.25, 0.40, 0.50, 0.45), II 1.70 (0.55, 0.25, 0.35, 0.30, 0.25), III 1.01 (0.40, 0.18, 0.25, 0.18), IV 1.75 (0.50, 0.25, 0.40, 0.35, 0.25). Leg formula: 1&gt; 4&gt; 2&gt; 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">
Cephalothorax. Sides of carapace yellowish-brown; dorsally yellow; chelicerae, sternum yellow; legs and abdomen light yellow. Carapace with a dark brown patch behind eyes, dorsally with a few rows of short hairs. Sides of carapace with finely longitudinal striae. Eyes six in two rows, rather large, nearly equally-sized, ALE slightly separated, touching posterior lateral eyes; posterior eyes in procurved row, touching each other (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F6848997" captionText="Figure 4. Opopaea apicalis (Simon, 1893). A. Carapace of male, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, lateral view; D. Genital area of female, dorsal view; E. Ventral scutum of female, ventral view; F. Right male chelicerae, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e67087.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/525067" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">4</figureCitation>
A and C). Base of fang with two plumose hairs on lateral sides (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F6848997" captionText="Figure 4. Opopaea apicalis (Simon, 1893). A. Carapace of male, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, lateral view; D. Genital area of female, dorsal view; E. Ventral scutum of female, ventral view; F. Right male chelicerae, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e67087.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/525067" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">4</figureCitation>
F). Labium wider than long, endites with membranous tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F6848997" captionText="Figure 4. Opopaea apicalis (Simon, 1893). A. Carapace of male, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, lateral view; D. Genital area of female, dorsal view; E. Ventral scutum of female, ventral view; F. Right male chelicerae, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e67087.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/525067" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">4</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">Legs. Leg I: femur with a row of dorsal setae, 3 retrolateral setae; patella without setae; tibia with a ventral seta; tarsus with distinct strong setae. Leg II, III and IV similar to leg I.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">Abdomen. Dorsal scutum oval-shaped, covering nearly entire abdominal length. Lobes on anterolateral corners of petiolar tube distinct, ridges developed, but without forming a scutal cove; opercula small, oval-shaped. Sperm pore clearly discernible, transverse.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">
Male palp. Patella of palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6849001" captionText="Figure 5. Opopaea apicalis (Simon, 1893). A. Left male palp in prolateral view, arrow ① points at clavate protrusion; B. Left male palp in retrolateral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e67087.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/538734" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">5</figureCitation>
A and B) significantly larger than cymbiobulbus; cymbiobulbus with a clavate protrusion at base and three branches at the end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">Female.</emphasis>
As in male, except as noted. Slightly larger than male. Measurements (in mm): Body length 1.35-1.45; carapace 0.40-0.60 length, 0.35-0.40 width; abdomen 0.50-0.65 length, 0.40-0.45 width. Leg measurements: I 1.88 (0.55, 0.25, 0.40, 0.48, 0.20), II 1.50 (0.50, 0.25, 0.30, 0.25, 0.20), III 1.38 (0.40, 0.20, 0.30, 0.30, 0.18), IV 1.79 (0.54, 0.30, 0.40, 0.35, 0.20).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">
Epigynum. Postgynal depression of epigastric area shallow, with inverted V-shaped sclerotisation situated posterior to epigastric furrow; parmula black, small (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F6848997" captionText="Figure 4. Opopaea apicalis (Simon, 1893). A. Carapace of male, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, lateral view; D. Genital area of female, dorsal view; E. Ventral scutum of female, ventral view; F. Right male chelicerae, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e67087.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/525067" pageId="0" pageNumber="67087">4</figureCitation>
D and E).
</paragraph>
